p: The oil sample was analyzed by using an Agilent 6890 gas chromatograph (Agilent, Santa Clara, CA, USA) equipped with flame ionization detector (FID, Agilent). Column: capillary column HP-5MS, 30 m × 0.25 mm × 0.25 μm film thickness. The GC oven temperature was programmed to stay at 60 °C for 1 min, heat to 200 °C at a rate of 15 °C/min, keep constant at 200 °C for 5 min, and then heat to 280 °C at a rate of 5 °C/min, and keep constant at 280 °C for 2 min [ 34].
